      <bridgehead renderas="sect4">Editing the flavor metadata in the Horizon dashboard</bridgehead>
      <para>These steps can be used to edit a flavor's metadata in the Horizon dashboard to add the
          <literal>extra_specs</literal> for a <literal>cpu_model</literal>:</para>

      <orderedlist>
        <listitem>
            <para>Access the Horizon dashboard and log in with admin credentials.</para>

         </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Access the Flavors menu by (A) clicking on the menu button, (B) navigating to the Admin
          section, and then (C) clicking on Flavors: </para>

            <mediaobject>
                  <imageobject role="fo"><imagedata fileref="media-hos.docs-operations-flavor_extraspecs_1.png" width="75%" format="PNG"/></imageobject><imageobject role="html"><imagedata fileref="media-hos.docs-operations-flavor_extraspecs_1.png"/></imageobject>
               </mediaobject>

         </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>In the list of flavors, choose the flavor you wish to edit and click on the entry under
          the Metadata column: </para>

            <mediaobject>
                  <imageobject role="fo"><imagedata fileref="media-hos.docs-operations-flavor_extraspecs_2.png" width="75%" format="PNG"/></imageobject><imageobject role="html"><imagedata fileref="media-hos.docs-operations-flavor_extraspecs_2.png"/></imageobject>
               </mediaobject>

            <note>
               <para>You can also create a new flavor and then choose that one to edit.</para>

            </note>
         </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>In the Custom field, enter <literal>hw:cpu_model</literal> and then click on the
            <literal>+</literal> (plus) sign to continue: </para>

            <mediaobject>
                  <imageobject role="fo"><imagedata fileref="media-hos.docs-operations-flavor_extraspecs_3.png" width="75%" format="PNG"/></imageobject><imageobject role="html"><imagedata fileref="media-hos.docs-operations-flavor_extraspecs_3.png"/></imageobject>
               </mediaobject>

         </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Then you will want to enter the CPU model into the field that you wish to use and then
          click Save: </para>

            <mediaobject>
                  <imageobject role="fo"><imagedata fileref="media-hos.docs-operations-flavor_extraspecs_4.png" width="75%" format="PNG"/></imageobject><imageobject role="html"><imagedata fileref="media-hos.docs-operations-flavor_extraspecs_4.png"/></imageobject>
               </mediaobject>

         </listitem>
      </orderedlist>
   

